    <text>
        <body>
            <div>
                <opener><salute>Dear Sir</salute> <dateline><placeName ref="pl0001">Downing</placeName> July 29<hi rend="superscript">th</hi>. 1787.</dateline></opener>
                <p>On the 3<hi rend="superscript">d</hi> of this month a parcel of drawings was sent to you &amp; I doubt not their safe arrival. you 
                    have now all the remainder. I think I have now done my duty fully &amp; think I may reserve <persName ref="pe0014">moses</persName>
                    to myself the <del><gap unit="letters" quantity="7" reason="illegible"/></del> rest of the year. I am sorry to reproach any person you 
                    have introduced to my acquaintance, but I think my treatment fr<hi rend="superscript">m</hi> <persName ref="pe0293">M<hi rend="superscript">r</hi> Burell</persName>
                    has not been of the <del><gap unit="letters" quantity="3" reason="illegible"/></del> most liberal kind. a Gentleman might at lest expect an answer to his
                    requests.</p>
                <p>Please make my Complim<hi rend="superscript">ts</hi> to miss Bulls<note xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude" type="editorial"><xi:include href="Bulls.xml"/></note>
                &amp; think me</p>
                <closer>
                    <salute>Dear Sir
                    <lb/>Y<hi rend="superscript">r</hi> faithful &amp; most
                    <lb/>obed<hi rend="superscript">t</hi> Serv<hi rend="superscript">t</hi></salute>
                    <signed><persName ref="pe0232">Tho. Pennant</persName></signed>
                  </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
